<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-08-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="391" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Brown</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 3.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-08-30"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 30, 1864</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatches No. 8, of the 23d, and No.
                            9, of the 29th ultimo, have been received, and it affords me pleasure to
                            express the department’s approval of your course in connexion with the
                            proceedings of the Sublime Porte against a bookstore in Constantinople
                            which had been used by some of the American missionaries there for the
                            sale of religious books. The settlement of this perplexing and painful
                            question has given much satisfaction.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John P. Brown</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Constantinople.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>